              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "bq. A larger value might lead to another problem. When a network partition causes some NM could not heartbeat with RM, these NM must kill containers running on it. If not, RM will complete containers running on them and notify corresponding AM when their RMNode transition to LOST state. And AM will launch another instance doing same things. Then there will be multiple instance problem.\nThis is expected already of all YARN apps already. Nothing specific to RM restarting. Nodes get lost all the time without properly shutting down - the apps are expected to handle races like this.\n\nYour current patch assumes Zookeeper setup, which is not true of all deployments.\n\nEven otherwise, your patch overall is definitely down the wrong path. As [~junping_du] said, we can increase the time-outs. We have HA specific time-outs like yarn.client.failover-retries | fail-over-max-attempt etc, you can increase them. Otherwise, if at all you need something, it will look like YARN-2344.\n\nI propose we close this as invalid.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=johna",
              "name": "johna",
              "key": "banjo",
              "avatarUrls": {
